# G-EOT-COHERENCE — end-of-turn coherence fix (2026-06-25)
# DIAGNOSIS (SP_EOT_DEBUG instrumentation): the end-of-turn token (<turn|>=106) reaches
# RANK 1 at a real turn boundary (e.g. after "Yes.") in our forward but loses by one
# position; with top_k=40/temp0.7 a rank-1 token is rarely drawn, so the model never
# stops and degenerates (fake user/model turns, foreign-script/HTML spam). NOT a weak
# model -- an us-issue (the eot logit a hair too low). Rank trajectory after "Yes.":
#   34940, 187, 24, 1, 965, ...   (best rank 1, never chosen)
# FIX: SP_EOT_BIAS adds a small fixed logit bias to the stop tokens (eos + <|turn>/<turn|>)
# so a rank-1 boundary tips to chosen, WITHOUT firing mid-answer (eot at rank ~1000).
# Default 0 = byte-identical null floor. Operating point SP_EOT_BIAS=4.0.
# ===== AFTER (SP_EOT_BIAS=4.0), coherent + stops cleanly: =====
Q: Is the sky blue? Answer in one word.
A: The sky is blue
--------------------------------------------------
Q: Tell me about the weather today.
A: Today is a sunny day. The temperature will be in the mid-60s with a light breeze from the west. There might be a chance of rain later on in the evening.
